# Trivy IaC allowlist — DELIBERATE architecture decisions, reviewed. Each is a
# HIGH "hardening" advisory that conflicts with the intended (lean, functional)
# design, not a real vulnerability. Re-review when the architecture changes.

# ALB is internet-facing BY DESIGN — it is CloudFront's `origin.<domain>` and is
# locked to CloudFront at the security-group level. Making it internal breaks the
# CDN → ALB path.
AVD-AWS-0053

# ECR image tags are mutable BY DESIGN — CD overwrites `:latest` (the task def
# references it). Every deploy also pushes an immutable `:<sha>` tag for audit/rollback.
AVD-AWS-0031

# Log + CloudTrail buckets use SSE-S3 (AES256), not a KMS CMK — acceptable for
# logs. The buckets holding actual data (docs) DO use the KMS CMK.
AVD-AWS-0132
AVD-AWS-0015

# App/DB security groups allow unrestricted EGRESS (0.0.0.0/0) — required: the app
# reaches RDS, S3, Bedrock, SES, and third-party APIs (Stripe/QBO/OpenRouter) via
# the NAT. Ingress is tightly restricted; egress-open is the intended posture.
AVD-AWS-0104
